Desktop




Dr. Ransom is President & CEO of Ransomshire Associates, Inc., a company supporting venture capital and early-stage companies in achieving business growth and successful exits.
With over 30 years of experience in the telecommunications industry, he was until 2005 the worldwide CTO of Alcatel and a member of its governing EXCOM. There he managed central activities encompassing corporate and product strategy, corporate research, R&D investment, M&A strategy and intellectual property. Prior to this he held various general management roles at Alcatel including managing Alcatel’s North American access and metro optical business. At BellSouth he directed an organization responsible for expanding BellSouth’s offerings into PCS wireless, IP, video, and advanced intelligent networks. At Bell Labs he managed an applied research organization that gave birth to a number of highly successful products in data and voice switching including the 5ESS system.
He currently serves as the Chairman of the Board of Teknovus, and on the board of directors of AMCC, Overture Networks, Ellacoya Networks, Turin Networks and CoreOptics.
Dr. Ransom has served as a member of the Technological Advisors Council of the U.S. Federal Communication Commission. He is co-author of the book, Broadband Access Technologies , published by McGraw-Hill.



