M. Niel Ransom Ph.D.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 7:35 AM ET
Communications Equipment

Company Overview of Polatis Incorporated



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
M. Niel Ransom Ph.D.Advisor and Director, Polatis IncorporatedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 10 Board Members in 10 different organizations across 15 different industries.See Board Relationships67--
Background

		Dr. M. Niel Ransom, Ph.D., serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Ransomshire Associates, Inc. Dr. Ransom founded Ransomshire Associates in 2005 where Dr. Ransom provides corporate strategy development and investment due diligence. He serves as an Advisor of Polatis Incorporated. Dr. Ransom served as the Chief Technology Officer of 3S Photonics S.A.S., since January 1, 2003 and Alcatel-Lucent, S.A. since 2003. Until 2005, he served as the worldwide Chief ... Technology Officer of Alcatel and Member of its governing EXCOM. Dr. Ransom was responsible for Alcatel Optronics's central activities directing a staff of 1200 encompassing corporate and product strategy, corporate research, R&D investment, M&A strategy and its intellectual property. He successfully oversaw the acquisition of TiMetra, Spatial Communications, eDial, PacketVideo, Thirdspace, iMagicTV, Right Vision, Telera, Aravox, WaterCove and Native Networks. Dr. Ransom held various general management roles at Alcatel including managing Alcatel’s access and metro optical business in North America achieving no.1 market share in DSL. He served as a Vice President and Chief Technology Officer of Alcatel Americas since June 2000. Dr. Ransom joined Alcatel in 1997 as a General Manager of the local networks business unit. During his tenure at Alcatel, his product strategy resulted in Alcatel achieving the No. 1 position worldwide in wireline access, optical networks, contact center solutions, IP-PBX and telecommunications satellites, as well as achieving the No. 2 position in edge routers. Prior to Alcatel, Dr. Ransom directed an organization (Advanced Technology Systems Center) responsible for expanding BellSouth's offerings into PCS wireless, IP data services, video entertainment and advanced intelligent networks. He started his career at Bell Labs, where he headed various development and served as a Member and eventually managed, an applied research organization that gave birth to a number of highly successful products in data, video and voice switching including the 5ESS system. He served as the Senior Director of Advanced Technology for Bell South. Prior to Bell South, he managed various development and applied research groups at&T Bell Labs. Dr. Ransom served as an Advisor of ANDevices, Inc. He serves on the advisory boards of several technology startups. He has been the Chairman of The Board of Saguna Networks Ltd. since February 23, 2015. Dr. Ransom served as the Chairman of Teknovus, Inc. He serves as a Director of MultiPhy, Ltd. (Multiphy Networks Ltd.). He has been a Director of Polatis Incorporated since June 2009. He has been a Director of Capella Photonics, Inc. since June 2011. He has been Independent Director of RadiSys Corporation since August 2010. He served as a Director of Cyan, Inc. from September 2009 to August 3, 2015. He served as a Director of DesignArt Networks Ltd. Dr. Ransom served on the Board of Turin Networks, AMCC, kbro. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at NetSocket, Inc. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Focus Ventures and Pond Venture Partners. He serves as a Member of Business Advisory Board at Quantenna Communications, Inc. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Carmel Ventures. He has been a Member of Advisory Board of Solomio Corporation since December 5, 2005. He served as Director of Overture Networks, Inc. Dr. Ransom served as a Director of Force10 Networks, Inc. since December 2007, Ellacoya Networks, Inc. since May 2007, CoreOptics GmbH since November 2007, ECI Telecom Ltd. from May 2006 to September 2007, Applied Micro Circuits Corporation from July 2006 to August 18, 2009. Dr. Ransom served as a Member of Advisory Council at AppTrigger, Inc. He served as a Member of the Technological Advisors Council of the U.S. Federal Communication Commission (FCC). Dr. Ransom has over 35 years of leadership experience in the telecommunications industry. He is a Co-Author of book, Broadband Access Technologies, published in 1999 by McGraw-Hill. Dr. Ransom has received numerous honors, is widely published. He holds five patents in telecommunications technology. Dr. Ransom holds a Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering from the University of Notre Dame, United States in 1973. He holds an Executive M.B.A. from the University of Chicago in 1986. Dr. Ransom also holds M.S.E.E. and B.S.E.E. degree from Old Dominion University in 1971 and 1970, respectively.Read Full Background




